  "firstAcquaintance": "A former rebel army hero who was captured while protecting her comrades. Subjected to the demon tribe's cruel experimentation and modification, leaving her mentally unstable.",
  "personality": "Eccentric and unhinged, consumed by thoughts of revenge. Despite this, she actually values teamwork and follows orders.",
  "like": "Hero storybooks",
  "familiarData": "During her time as a wanderer, she possessed formidable strength capable of fighting one against a hundred. However, her excessive activity drew the attention of the Demon Lord. During the ensuing attack, Koge stayed behind to hold off the enemy forces, ultimately being captured alive.\nAfter waking up, she was subjected to the demon army's cruel experiments and modifications. No matter how painful the experiments were, she would always smile. Her strong body and spirit only prolonged her suffering.\nThe demons underestimated Koge's desire for revenge. Discarded as a failed experiment, she tenaciously survived and successfully escaped the laboratory.\nThough she survived, her right ear and left hand were replaced with mechanical parts, and she was cursed to never show any expression other than a smile. Whether in battle or in tears, Koge's mouth is always frozen in a grin.\nThe cruel experiences and curse cause Koge to burst into laughter from time to time. Many times it's hard to tell whether she's genuinely happy or if it's the curse causing her mental instability. Whenever someone asks how she's feeling, she always responds: \"Do I look unhappy?\"",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
